sequenceDiagram
  %% Evidence: middleware/tenant.rs, services/rate_limit.rs, services/quota.rs, services/rls.rs, migration 0009
  actor Client
  participant TenantMW as Tenant middleware
  participant DB as PostgreSQL
  participant Limits as Redis / quota services
  participant Handler
  participant RLS as Tenant SQL context + forced RLS

  Client->>TenantMW: Bearer token + X-Organization-Id
  TenantMW->>TenantMW: Verify token and parse organization UUID
  TenantMW->>DB: Load active organization + active membership for claims.sub
  alt Membership valid
    DB-->>TenantMW: TenantContext with database role
    TenantMW->>Limits: Organization/user rate limit and API quota
    Limits-->>TenantMW: Allow
    TenantMW->>Handler: Claims + TenantContext
    Handler->>Handler: Organization RBAC / ownership / lifecycle
    Handler->>RLS: Set organization and user context
    RLS->>DB: Query under forced RLS policy
    DB-->>Handler: Tenant-matching rows
    Handler-->>Client: Response
  else Missing, inactive, or mismatched membership
    DB-->>TenantMW: No row
    TenantMW-->>Client: 403 Forbidden
  end
  Note over Handler,RLS: Explicit platform bypass is separate and does not follow automatically from super_admin or owner
